There is a question: "If the value of the algebraic expression $5a+3b$ is $-4$, then what is the value of the algebraic expression $2\left(a+b\right)+4\left(2a+b\right)$?" Tang, who loves to use his brain, solved the problem as follows:  
Original expression $=2a+2b+8a+4b=10a+6b=2\left(5a+3b\right)=2\times \left(-4\right)=-8$  
Tang treated $5a+3b$ as a whole to solve it. Treating expressions as a whole is an important method in solving problems in high school mathematics. Please follow the method above to complete the following questions:  
$(1)$ Given $a^{2}+a=3$, then $2a^{2}+2a+2023=$______;  
$(2)$ Given $a-2b=-3$, find the value of $3\left(a-b\right)-7a+11b+2$;  
$(3)$ Given $a^{2}+2ab=-5$, $ab-2b^{2}=-3$, find the value of the algebraic expression $a^{2}+ab+2b^{2}$.

